DocumentBuilderFactory factory = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();
DocumentBuilder builder = factory.newDocumentBuilder();
Use the DocumentBuilder instance to parse the XML document and create a Document object. This object represents the entire XML document and provides methods for accessing its different elements and attributes.

File xmlFile = new File("messages.xml");
Document doc = builder.parse(xmlFile);
Use the Document object to access the different elements and attributes in the XML document. For example, to access all the message elements, you can use the getElementsByTagName method and loop through the resulting NodeList:

NodeList messageList = doc.getElementsByTagName("message");
for (int i = 0; i < messageList.getLength(); i++) {
    Element message = (Element) messageList.item(i);
